Diagnosis.
Male distinguished from other species of subgenus 

Gnathonomia

as follows: apical margin of T1–5 without conspicuous white bands (
Fig. 1c, 1e
); T2–4 with apical hair bands reduced, restricted to lateral edges (
Fig. 1e
); upper lateral surface of propodeum with sparse, coarse punctures, narrow shiny interspaces (
Fig. 1e
); hind femur slightly developed (
Fig. 1b, 1d
); penis valve with hooked projection basically (
Fig. 2a
).
